# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-feature readiness evidence — regenerable per-run test output.
#
# Ignore by directory ROLE, per the transient/durable SDD artifact taxonomy
# (ADR-0018; canonical doc: FS-GG/FS.GG.SDD docs/reference/artifact-taxonomy.md).
# This one role rule replaces the former ~100 per-feature `!…/readiness/**`
# re-inclusion exceptions; the small, explicitly-justified set of durable pins
# below is the only exception (#84 / FS.GG.SDD#110).
specs/*/readiness/

# --- Durable readiness pins — committed test FIXTURES, not per-run output -----
# Each tree below is READ by the test suite (File.ReadAllText + token/equality
# asserts) and is NOT regenerated by `dotnet test`, so a clean checkout without
# it fails those tests. Kept committed per the taxonomy's "pin durable proofs
# rarely, justified inline" rule. Grouped by what reads them.
#
#   Gate lane (runs on every PR):
#     093 — parity goldens compared by Controls.Tests (regen env-gated: PARITY_REGEN).
#     151 — regression-evidence/limitations read by Testing.Tests + Rendering.Harness.Tests.
!specs/093-visual-state-style-layer/readiness/
!specs/093-visual-state-style-layer/readiness/**
!specs/151-complete-p8-layout/readiness/
!specs/151-complete-p8-layout/readiness/**
#
#   Release lane (Package.Tests, release-only): harness-generated compatibility
#   ledgers / validation summaries / fsi transcripts, read + token-asserted.
#   Regenerated via Rendering.Harness (scripts/emit-harness-readiness.sh), not
#   by `dotnet test` — the reader tests intentionally avoid the harness exe.
!specs/035-api-discovery-names/readiness/
!specs/035-api-discovery-names/readiness/**
!specs/036-archive-readiness-api-docs/readiness/
!specs/036-archive-readiness-api-docs/readiness/**
!specs/142-harfbuzz-text-shaping/readiness/
!specs/142-harfbuzz-text-shaping/readiness/**
!specs/146-render-anywhere-protocol/readiness/
!specs/146-render-anywhere-protocol/readiness/**
!specs/147-compositor-damage-redraw/readiness/
!specs/147-compositor-damage-redraw/readiness/**
!specs/148-compositor-live-integration/readiness/
!specs/148-compositor-live-integration/readiness/**
!specs/149-complete-compositor-p7/readiness/
!specs/149-complete-compositor-p7/readiness/**
!specs/150-intrinsic-layout-protocol/readiness/
!specs/150-intrinsic-layout-protocol/readiness/**
!specs/152-compositor-live-proof/readiness/
!specs/152-compositor-live-proof/readiness/**
!specs/153-compositor-proof-interpreter/readiness/
!specs/153-compositor-proof-interpreter/readiness/**
!specs/154-compositor-proof-acceptance/readiness/
!specs/154-compositor-proof-acceptance/readiness/**
!specs/155-native-proof-capture/readiness/
!specs/155-native-proof-capture/readiness/**
!specs/156-same-profile-timing/readiness/
!specs/156-same-profile-timing/readiness/**
!specs/157-no-clear-damage-scissor/readiness/
!specs/157-no-clear-damage-scissor/readiness/**
!specs/158-separate-proof-timing/readiness/
!specs/158-separate-proof-timing/readiness/**
!specs/159-layer-promotion-keys/readiness/
!specs/159-layer-promotion-keys/readiness/**
!specs/160-performance-validation-throughput/readiness/
!specs/160-performance-validation-throughput/readiness/**
!specs/161-host-performance-lane-ledger/readiness/
!specs/161-host-performance-lane-ledger/readiness/**
!specs/163-package-feed-validation-lanes/readiness/
!specs/163-package-feed-validation-lanes/readiness/**
#
#   168 — surface-baselines/Rendering.Harness.SkillParity.txt is the FSI-surface golden
#         Feature168 (Rendering.Harness.Tests) compares against the live SkillParity.fsi;
#         it is NOT regenerated by `dotnet test`. The rest of 168's readiness is transient
#         (lane logs, TestResults, package-feed assets), so pin ONLY the durable subtree:
#         re-admit the dir, re-ignore its contents, then re-admit surface-baselines/.
!specs/168-skill-parity-evidence/readiness/
specs/168-skill-parity-evidence/readiness/**
!specs/168-skill-parity-evidence/readiness/surface-baselines/
!specs/168-skill-parity-evidence/readiness/surface-baselines/**
!specs/207-ui-bom-metapackage/readiness/
!specs/207-ui-bom-metapackage/readiness/**
#
#   Authored source-of-truth prose (not machine-regenerated; kept so a clean
#   checkout retains it even though no test reads it back from disk):
#     209 — version-coherence-scenarios.md mirrored by the Feature209 coherence tests.
!specs/209-version-staleness-guard/readiness/
!specs/209-version-staleness-guard/readiness/**

# Regenerable roles that can appear INSIDE a pinned durable tree — keep ignored
# regardless of the pins above (ADR-0018 regenerable roles). Unanchored, so they
# match at any depth; this replaces the former per-feature nuget-cache/ re-excludes.
# NB: Rendering deliberately does NOT adopt the SDD fragment's root-anchored
# `readiness/*/` role — this repo's readiness lives under specs/<feature>/readiness/
# (handled above), and the only root readiness/* trees (readiness/surface-baselines,
# readiness/parity) are durable + gate-checked, so a root role rule would wrongly
# ignore them.
nuget-cache/
.tmp/

